# Testing & Quality Assurance

## Test runner (MANDATORY)

Always use the wrapper script — never call pytest directly:

```bash
scripts/run_tests.sh                              # Full suite
scripts/run_tests.sh tests/gateway/               # Subsystem
scripts/run_tests.sh tests/tools/test_delegate.py::TestBlockedTools  # Specific test
```

The wrapper normalizes: credentials, HOME, timezone, locale, worker count.
Bare pytest = inconsistent results across environments.

## Lint

```bash
.venv/bin/ruff check .
```

Critical violations (F821 undefined name, F811 unused import) must be fixed before commit.

## Environment setup

```bash
source .venv/bin/activate  # or: source venv/bin/activate
```

The wrapper probes `.venv`, `venv`, and the shared Hermes checkout venv automatically.

## Test invariants

- Tests MUST NOT write to a real `~/.hermes/` — use existing fixtures with `HERMES_HOME` override
- Tests MUST NOT depend on network calls (mock external APIs)
- Tests MUST NOT depend on specific file mtimes (use fixture factories)
- Tests MUST be idempotent (running twice = same result)

## Key fixture patterns

| Fixture | Purpose | Location |
|---------|---------|----------|
| `tmp_hermes_home` | Isolated HERMES_HOME | conftest.py |
| `mock_registry` | Fake AGENT_REGISTRY.json | tests/conftest.py |
| `mock_knowledge` | Fake knowledge layer state | tests/conftest.py |
| `mock_together_api` | Mocked Together AI responses | tests/gateway/ |

## Coverage expectations

- Core modules (decision_engine, selector, scoring): high coverage required
- Tool implementations: medium coverage
- CLI slash commands: basic smoke tests
- Plugins: isolated plugin tests

## Test categories

| Directory | Tests | CI Required |
|-----------|-------|-------------|
| tests/tools/ | Built-in tool dispatch | Yes |
| tests/gateway/ | Gateway messaging, auth | Yes |
| tests/ (root) | Integration, regression | Yes |
| tests/research/ | Research harness (slow) | Optional |

## When to run tests

- Before ANY commit (at minimum, affected subsystem)
- After modifying agent registry (enum breakage risk)
- After modifying tool dispatch (blocked-tool enforcement)
- After modifying production scripts (regression risk)
- After modifying governance files (routing policy tests)

## CI integration (when budget allows)

GitHub Actions workflows in `.github/`:
- Unit tests (all platforms)
- Lint (ruff)
- Type check (mypy)
- Security audit (pip-audit)
- Container smoke test (Docker build)

Currently budget-blocked until ~June 1. Local tests are canonical.

## Anti-patterns

- Do NOT skip tests before committing ("it's just a docs change" — docs can break imports)
- Do NOT use pytest directly (env normalization matters)
- Do NOT write tests that depend on production data paths (use fixtures)
- Do NOT ignore flaky tests (investigate: timing? network? fixture leak?)
- Do NOT hardcode dates in test assertions (use relative or fixture dates)